J enkin in Welsh pedigrees is often used as the Welsh form of John, and the text shews it to be so in this case. John or Jenkin Basset, of Beaupre‚ who died 1492, was succeeded by his eldest son James‚ whose daughter and heiress Elinor married Sir Rice Mansel, but the male heir was william, second son of John or Jenkin, and the granter of the above quit-claim. He did not inherit Beaupre, and is therefore styled generosus instead of armiger; but the messuage in the castle baillie was part of the male fief, being one of the lodgings provided for the tenants in capite when they were in residence to discharge their duty of castle guard.
